==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Equability
<hw>E`qua*bil"i*ty</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>aequabilitas</ets>, fr. <ets>aequabilis</ets>. See
<er>Equable</er>.]</ety> <def>The quality or condition of being equable;
evenness or uniformity; <as>as, <ex>equability</ex> of temperature; the
<ex>equability</ex> of the mind.</as></def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>For the celestial bodies, the <qex>equability</qex> and constancy
of their motions argue them ordained by wisdom.</q>
<rj><qau>Ray.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Equable</ent>⟦br⟧
